>
  <p>
    Yes, Costco hot dogs are 100% beef. They are made with USDA Choice or better grade beef and contain no pork, chicken, turkey, or other meats. Costco produces their hot dogs in-house to maintain quality control and keep the price at $1.50.
  </p>

  <h2>USDA Choice Grade Beef</h2>
  <p>
    The beef used in Costco hot dogs is USDA Choice or better. To understand what this means:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>USDA Prime:</strong> The highest grade, representing about 3% of graded beef. Exceptional marbling and tenderness.</li>
    <li><strong>USDA Choice:</strong> High-quality beef with moderate marbling. Represents about 50% of graded beef and is the standard for most premium products.</li>
    <li><strong>USDA Select:</strong> Leaner beef with less marbling. Still high quality but less tender and flavorful.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    By using Choice or better grade beef, Costco ensures their hot dogs have good flavor and texture without the premium price of Prime.
  </p>

  <h2>Why 100% Beef Matters</h2>
  <p>
    Many conventional hot dogs use a blend of meats or meat byproducts to reduce costs. Common alternatives include:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Pork and beef blends</li>
    <li>Chicken or turkey fillers</li>
    <li>Mechanically separated meat</li>
    <li>Soy protein extenders</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Costco's commitment to 100% beef means you're getting a higher quality product. There are no fillers, no mechanically separated meat, and no meat byproducts.
  </p>

  <h2>In-House Production</h2>
  <p>
    Costco operates its own hot dog manufacturing facilities, primarily in the Chicago area (a historic hot dog production hub). This vertical integration allows them to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Control quality at every step</li>
    <li>Keep costs low by eliminating the middleman</li>
    <li>Maintain consistent supply across all warehouses</li>
    <li>Protect the $1.50 price point even when commodity prices fluctuate</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Conclusion</h2>
  <p>
    Costco hot dogs are genuinely 100% beef, made with quality USDA Choice grade meat. The simple ingredient list and in-house production are key reasons why they've maintained their reputation for quality despite the incredibly low $1.50 price point. If you're looking for a straightforward, no-surprises hot dog, Costco's offering is hard to beat.
  </p>
</FAQLayout>
